    "content": "## Your Area Assignment\n\n**Area:** agentic-docs-and-workflows\n**Description:** Agentic system documentation (architecture overview, JSON definitions, knowledge system, skills, workflows) plus workflow definitions and example skills.\n**File patterns:** [\"agentic/rules/docs/*.md\", \"agentic/workflows/*.json\", \"agentic/skills/example-skill/SKILL.md\"]\n\n## Plan Summary\n\nAreas in the plan:\n- core-application: The monolithic main application file containing FileScanner, MergeEngine, EditorHistoryExtractor, SQLite persistence layer, and Flask web routes — the entire business logic of the file recovery and merge tool.\n- web-templates: Jinja2 HTML templates for the Flask web UI — setup wizard, file browser, inventory, conflict resolution, merge editor, coverage dashboard, and progress pages using Bootstrap 5 dark theme.\n- agentic-engine: Core engine for autonomous AI agent workflows — OpenRouter API client, workflow runner, agentic loop (ReAct and native tool-calling), tool executor, and knowledge/skills resolver.\n- agentic-tools: Tool implementations and JSON definitions for the agentic engine — file tree walking, directory listing, file reading/writing, and code search tools that agents can invoke.\n- agentic-docs-and-workflows: Agentic system documentation (architecture overview, JSON definitions, knowledge system, skills, workflows) plus workflow definitions and example skills.\n- claude-config-and-rules: Project-level Claude Code configuration — rules index, coding rules (invariants, testing, bug-fixing), skills (code-documenter, code-search), spark configuration, and test plan infrastructure.\n- project-root-and-scripts: Top-level project files — CLAUDE.md project overview, PowerShell recovery script, commands reference, version marker, and git configuration.\n\n## Instructions\n\nAnalyze all files matching your area's patterns. Return a JSON report with `area`, `files`, `area_summary`, `cross_area_refs`, and optionally `suggested_splits`."
