g the tests/history directory for archived completed test plans.\n    Exports: []\n    Imports from: []\n\n### Area: agentic-tools\n\n**Summary:** This area implements a set of filesystem and code search tools for the agentic engine. It follows a consistent pattern where each tool is a standalone module with an `execute()` function that accepts parameters plus a `_base_dir` for security sandboxing. All tools return JSON strings for easy integration with the agentic workflow system. The tools include file reading/writing, directory listing, file tree generation, and regex-based code search, with built-in path validation to prevent directory traversal attacks. The definitions.json provides the schema that the agentic engine uses to discover and invoke these tools.\n\n**Cross-area references:** []\n\n**Files:**\n  - **agentic/tools/__init__.py** (utility): Package initialization file for the agentic tools module with module-level docstring.\n    Exports: []\n    Imports from: []\n  - **agentic/tools/definitions.json** (config): JSON schema defining 5 agentic tools (read_file, write_file, list_directory, search_code, get_file_tree) with parameter schemas and tool set groupings for code_analysis and file_ops.\n    Exports: []\n    Imports from: []\n  - **agentic/tools/get_file_tree.py** (utility): Generates an indented text representation of the directory tree, respecting depth limits and skipping common build/cache directories.\n    Exports: [\"execute(max_depth=4, include_hidden=False, _base_dir='.', **kwargs) -> str\"]\n    Imports from: [\"json from stdlib\", \"os from stdlib\", \"Path from pathlib\"]\n  - **agentic/tools/list_directory.py** (utility): Lists files and directories with optional recursive traversal up to depth 3, with path escaping protection.\n    Exports: [\"execute(path='.', recursive=False, _base_dir='.', **kwargs) -> str\"]\n    Imports from: [\"json from stdlib\", \"os from stdlib\"]\n  - **agentic/tools/read_file.py** (utility): Reads file contents with optional line range selection and path escaping protection.\n    Exports: [\"execute(path, start_line=None, end_line=None, _base_dir='.', **kwargs) -> str\"]\n    Imports from: [\"json from stdlib\", \"os from stdlib\"]\n  - **agentic/tools/search_code.py** (utility): Performs regex search across files with file pattern filtering, skipping common cache/build directories, and limits results to 100 matches.\n    Exports: [\"execute(pattern, file_pattern=None, path='.', _base_dir='.', **kwargs) -> str\"]\n    Imports from: [\"fnmatch from stdlib\", \"json from stdlib\", \"os from stdlib\", \"re from stdlib\"]\n  - **agentic/tools/write_file.py** (utility): Writes content to a file, automatically creating parent directories, with path escaping protection.\n    Exports: [\"execute(path, content, _base_dir='.', **kwargs) -> str\"]\n    Imports from: [\"json from stdlib\", \"os from stdlib\"]\n\n### Area: web-templates\n\n**Summary:** The web-templates area provides a complete Jinja2 template suite for the Flask-based File Recovery Merger application. It uses Bootstrap 5 with a dark theme and implements a multi-page workflow: setup wizard, file browser with tree navigation, inventory table, conflict resolution (list and detail views), interactive merge editor with hunk-level control, coverage dashboard, and real-time progress pages using Server-Sent Events. The templates follow a consistent inheritance pattern from base.html, share common CSS for diff visualization and status badges, and implement rich client-side JavaScript for keyboard navigation, AJAX resolution, and dynamic content loading.\n\n**Cross-area references:** [\"imports Flask route handlers from core-application (/setup, /browse, /inventory, /conflicts, /conflict/*, /merge/*, /resolve*, /execute, /api/*, /scan-events, /merge-events, /extract-events, /log, /export-log, /extract-history)\", \"uses Bootstrap 5.3.3 CSS and JS from CDN\", \"uses Jinja2 template engine features (extends, block, for, if, with, tojson filter)\"]\n\n**Files:**\n  - **templates/base.html** (template): Base HTML template providing the common layout with Bootstrap 5 dark theme, navigation bar, flash message handling, and extensible blocks for all child templates.\n    Exports: [\"base template with blocks: title, content, extra_css, extra_js\"]\n    Imports from: [\"Bootstrap 5.3.3 CSS/JS from CDN\"]\n  - **templates/setup.html** (template): Setup wizard for configuring source directories, target directory, project filters, and ignore patterns with session management and dynamic source addition.\n    Exports: [\"setup form template\"]\n    Imports from: [\"extends base.html\", \"POST /setup endpoint\"]\n  - **templates/browse.html** (template): Interactive file browser with resizable sidebar, expandable directory tree, version selection, conflict resolution, and keyboard shortcuts for rapid file review.\n    Exports: [\"file browser interface\"]\n    Imports from: [\"extends base.html\", \"/api/browse-tree endpoint\", \"/resolve endpoint\", \"/resolve-toggle endpoint\", \"/resolve-accept-defaults endpoint\", \"/execute endpoint\"]\n  - **templates/inventory.html** (template): Tabular inventory view with pagination, sorting, filtering by category, and action buttons for executing auto-merges and resolved conflicts.\n    Exports: [\"inventory table view\"]\n    Imports from: [\"extends base.html\", \"/execute endpoint\"]\n  - **templates/conflicts.html** (template): Conflict resolution overview showing progress bar, list of all conflicts with status, and bulk auto-resolve functionality.\n    Exports: [\"conflict list view\"]\n    Imports from: [\"extends base.html\", \"/resolve-all-latest endpoint\", \"/execute endpoint\"]\n  - **templates/conflict_detail.html** (template): Detailed conflict resolution page with version metadata cards, side-by-side and unified diff views, and keyboard shortcuts for rapid resolution.\n    Exports: [\"single conflict resolution page\"]\n    Imports from: [\"extends base.html\", \"/resolve endpoint\", \"/merge endpoint\"]\n  - **templates/merge_editor.html** (template): Advanced merge editor allowing per-hunk selection (left/right/both/neither), full text editing mode, and saving custom merged results.\n    Exports: [\"interactive merge editor\"]\n    Imports from: [\"extends base.html\", \"/api/save-merge endpoint\"]\n  - **templates/coverage.html** (template): Coverage dashboard showing per-source statistics with visual progress bars and expandable file lists categorized by unique, identical, and conflict status.\n    Exports: [\"source coverage dashboard\"]\n    Imports from: [\"extends base.html\", \"/api/coverage-files endpoint\"]\n  - **templates/scan_progress.html** (template): Real-time scan progress page using SSE to display file discovery, scanning status, and completion statistics with animated progress bar.\n    Exports: [\"scan progress page\"]\n    Imports from: [\"extends base.html\", \"/scan-events SSE endpoint\"]\n  - **templates/merge_progress.html** (template): Real-time merge execution progress with SSE updates, showing new files, updated files, skipped files, errors, and detailed completion report.\n    Exports: [\"merge execution progress page\"]\n    Imports from: [\"extends base.html\", \"/merge-events SSE endpoint\"]\n  - **templates/extract_progress.html** (template): Real-time progress page for extracting files from editor history (Windsurf/VS Code/Cursor) with SSE updates and completion statistics.\n    Exports: [\"editor history extraction progress\"]\n    Imports from: [\"extends base.html\", \"/extract-events SSE endpoint\"]\n  - **templates/extract_history.html** (template): Setup page for extracting files from editor history with auto-detected history sources and configurable filters.\n    Exports: [\"editor history extraction setup\"]\n    Imports from: [\"extends base.html\", \"POST /extract-history endpoint\"]\n  - **templates/log.html** (template): Action log showing merge results, file operations, timestamps, and recovery suggestions with JSON export capability.\n    Exports: [\"action log and results view\"]\n    Imports from: [\"extends base.html\", \"/export-log endpoint\"]\n  - **templates/_file_detail.html** (template): Partial template for the file detail panel in the browse view, showing version metadata, diff views, and quick resolution controls.\n    Exports: [\"file detail panel partial\"]\n    Imports from: [\"included by browse.html\", \"/resolve endpoint\", \"/api/file-content endpoint\", \"/api/file-detail endpoint\"]\n\n\n## Current Area Plan\n\n```json\n[\n  {\n    \"name\": \"core-application\",\n    \"description\": \"The monolithic main application file containing FileScanner, MergeEngine, EditorHistoryExtractor, SQLite persistence layer, and Flask web routes \\u2014 the entire business logic of the file recovery and merge tool.\",\n    \"file_patterns\": [\n      \"file_merger.py\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"web-templates\",\n    \"description\": \"Jinja2 HTML templates for the Flask web UI \\u2014 setup wizard, file browser, inventory, conflict resolution, merge editor, coverage dashboard, and progress pages using Bootstrap 5 dark theme.\",\n    \"file_patterns\": [\n      \"templates/*.html\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"agentic-engine\",\n    \"description\": \"Core engine for autonomous AI agent workflows \\u2014 OpenRouter API client, workflow runner, agentic loop (ReAct and native tool-calling), tool executor, and knowledge/skills resolver.\",\n    \"file_patterns\": [\n      \"agentic/engine/__init__.py\",\n      \"agentic/engine/knowledge.py\",\n      \"agentic/engine/loop.py\",\n      \"agentic/engine/openrouter.py\",\n      \"agentic/engine/runner.py\",\n      \"agentic/engine/tool_executor.py\",\n      \"agentic/README.md\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"agentic-tools\",\n    \"description\": \"Tool implementations and JSON definitions for the agentic engine \\u2014 file tree walking, directory listing, file reading/writing, and code search tools that agents can invoke.\",\n    \"file_patterns\": [\n      \"agentic/tools/__init__.py\",\n      \"agentic/tools/definitions.json\",\n      \"agentic/tools/get_file_tree.py\",\n      \"agentic/tools/list_directory.py\",\n      \"agentic/tools/read_file.py\",\n      \"agentic/tools/search_code.py\",\n      \"agentic/tools/write_file.py\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"agentic-docs-and-workflows\",\n    \"description\": \"Agentic system documentation (architecture overview, JSON definitions, knowledge system, skills, workflows) plus workflow definitions and example skills.\",\n    \"file_patterns\": [\n      \"agentic/rules/docs/*.md\",\n      \"agentic/workflows/*.json\",\n      \"agentic/skills/example-skill/SKILL.md\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"claude-config-and-rules\",\n    \"description\": \"Project-level Claude Code configuration \\u2014 rules index, coding rules (invariants, testing, bug-fixing), skills (code-documenter, code-search), spark configuration, and test plan infrastructure.\",\n    \"file_patterns\": [\n      \".claude/RULES_INDEX.md\",\n      \".claude/rules/invariants.md\",\n      \".claude/rules/testing.md\",\n      \".claude/rules/bug-fixing.md\",\n      \".claude/rules/docs/.gitkeep\",\n      \".claude/skills/code-documenter/SKILL.md\",\n      \".claude/skills/code-search/SKILL.md\",\n      \".claude/settings.local.json\",\n      \".claude/spark_config.json\",\n      \".claude/spark_plans/*.json\",\n      \".claude/tests/.gitkeep\",\n      \".claude/tests/history/.gitkeep\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"project-root-and-scripts\",\n    \"description\": \"Top-level project files \\u2014 CLAUDE.md project overview, PowerShell recovery script, commands reference, version marker, and git configuration.\",\n    \"file_patterns\": [\n      \"CLAUDE.md\",\n      \"restore_deleted_files.ps1\",\n      \"commands.txt\",\n      \"0.12.0\",\n      \".gitignore\"\n    ]\n  }\n]\n```\n\n\n