    "content": "## Repository Structure\n\n```\nGuanine(CodeEdit)/\n├── agentic/\n│   ├── engine/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py\n│   │   ├── knowledge.py\n│   │   ├── loop.py\n│   │   ├── openrouter.py\n│   │   ├── runner.py\n│   │   └── tool_executor.py\n│   ├── rules/\n│   │   └── docs/\n│   │       ├── agentic-overview.md\n│   │       ├── json-definitions.md\n│   │       ├── knowledge-system.md\n│   │       ├── skills.md\n│   │       └── workflows.md\n│   ├── skills/\n│   │   └── example-skill/\n│   │       └── SKILL.md\n│   ├── tools/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py\n│   │   ├── definitions.json\n│   │   ├── get_file_tree.py\n│   │   ├── list_directory.py\n│   │   ├── read_file.py\n│   │   ├── search_code.py\n│   │   └── write_file.py\n│   ├── workflows/\n│   │   └── example_workflow.json\n│   └── README.md\n├── sessions/\n├── templates/\n│   ├── _file_detail.html\n│   ├── base.html\n│   ├── browse.html\n│   ├── conflict_detail.html\n│   ├── conflicts.html\n│   ├── coverage.html\n│   ├── extract_history.html\n│   ├── extract_progress.html\n│   ├── inventory.html\n│   ├── log.html\n│   ├── merge_editor.html\n│   ├── merge_progress.html\n│   ├── scan_progress.html\n│   └── setup.html\n├── 0.12.0\n├── CLAUDE.md\n├── commands.txt\n├── file_merger.py\n└── restore_deleted_files.ps1\n```\n\n## Repository Metadata\n\n```json\n{\n  \"total_files\": 89,\n  \"total_lines\": 126088,\n  \"languages\": {\n    \"python\": 39,\n    \"markdown\": 14,\n    \"html\": 14,\n    \"json\": 6,\n    \"powershell\": 1\n  },\n  \"top_level_directories\": [\n    \".claude\",\n    \".code-index\",\n    \"agentic\",\n    \"templates\"\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n## Documentation Mode\n\nMode: **fill-gaps**\n\n## Previous Explorer Summaries\n\n### Area: agentic-docs-and-workflows\nThis area contains the complete documentation and configuration for the agentic workflow engine. The five markdown documents in agentic/rules/docs/ provide self-contained reference material covering system architecture, JSON workflow definitions, the knowledge injection system, skill creation, and workflow execution. The example_workflow.json demonstrates a practical two-layer workflow, while the example-skill/SKILL.md serves as a template for creating folder-based skills. Together these files enable developers to build autonomous AI agents without reading the engine source code, following a documentation-first approach with YAML frontmatter metadata, progressive disclosure patterns, and JSON-configurable layer pipelines.\nCross-area refs: [\"References agentic/engine/runner.py from json-definitions.md\", \"References agentic/engine/knowledge.py from knowledge-system.md and skills.md\", \"References agentic/engine/loop.py from agentic-overview.md\", \"References agentic/tools/definitions.json from agentic-overview.md\", \"References agentic/skills/ directory structure from skills.md\", \"References agentic/skill_definitions/ directory from skills.md\", \"References agentic/workflows/ directory from agentic-overview.md\", \"References OpenRouterClient from agentic-overview.md and json-definitions.md\", \"References run_workflow function from agentic-overview.md and json-definitions.md\", \"References LightweightWorkflowSession from json-definitions.md and workflows.md\", \"References process_agentic_loop and process_agentic_loop_native from workflows.md\", \"References execute_tool_call from workflows.md\", \"References tools: read_file, write_file, list_directory, search_code, get_file_tree from agentic-overview.md and example-skill/SKILL.md\", \"References use_skill tool from knowledge-system.md\", \"References agentic.tools.my_module.execute pattern from json-definitions.md\"]\nSuggested splits: []\n\n### Area: project-root-and-scripts\nThis area contains top-level project metadata and utility scripts. CLAUDE.md serves as the central project documentation and rule discovery entry point, describing a monolithic Flask application for file recovery and merging. The PowerShell script provides a standalone CLI alternative for history extraction without the web interface. The remaining files are operational artifacts: session resume notes, a version marker (likely accidental), and git configuration. The area follows a documentation-as-code approach with decentralized rule discovery rather than centralized configuration.\nCross-area refs: [\"restore_deleted_files.ps1 references EditorHistoryExtractor logic from core-application (file_merger.py)\", \"CLAUDE.md documents architecture of core-application (FileScanner, MergeEngine, EditorHistoryExtractor classes)\", \"CLAUDE.md references web-templates (templates/ directory with 14 Jinja2 files)\", \"CLAUDE.md references claude-config-and-rules (.claude/rules/, .claude/skills/ directories)\", \"commands.txt references spark/init.py from claude-config-and-rules area\"]\nSuggested splits: []\n\n### Area: core-application\nThe core-application area is a single-file monolithic Flask application that implements the complete business logic of a file recovery and merge tool. It follows a layered architecture with data models (FileVersion, MergeItem, SourceConfig), core services (FileScanner, MergeEngine, EditorHistoryExtractor), persistence (SQLite with WAL mode), and web controllers (Flask routes). The application supports scanning multiple source directories including IDE editor history folders, detecting file conflicts via SHA256 hashing, presenting side-by-side diffs, and executing merges with full audit logging. Session state is persisted to SQLite with automatic migration from legacy JSON formats. Background operations use threading with progress queues streamed to the UI via Server-Sent Events.\nCross-area refs: [\"imports render_template, request, redirect, url_for, jsonify, Response, stream_with_context, flash from flask (web-templates area depends on these routes)\", \"imports Markup from markupsafe (used by Jinja2 templates in web-templates area)\", \"templates referenced: setup.html, scan_progress.html, inventory.html, conflicts.html, conflict_detail.html, merge_progress.html, log.html, browse.html, _file_detail.html, merge_editor.html, coverage.html, extract_history.html, extract_progress.html (all in web-templates area)\"]\nSuggested splits: [{\"suggestion\": \"Split into modular packages\", \"rationale\": \"At 2861 lines, file_merger.py is a large monolith. It could be split into: (1) models/ (dataclasses FileVersion, MergeItem, SourceConfig), (2) services/ (FileScanner, MergeEngine, EditorHistoryExtractor, RecoveryAdvisor), (3) persistence/ (SQLite session management), (4) routes/ (Flask blueprints for setup, inventory, conflicts, merge, coverage, history extraction), (5) utils/ (diff generation, file utilities). This would improve maintainability and testability.\"}, {\"suggestion\": \"Extract EditorHistoryExtractor to standalone module\", \"rationale\": \"The EditorHistoryExtractor class (~300 lines) with its Windsurf/VS Code/Cursor detection logic is a distinct domain that could be reused independently. It has clear boundaries and minimal coupling to the rest of the application.\"}, {\"suggestion\": \"Extract persistence layer\", \"rationale\": \"The SQLite persistence code (~500 lines) including _get_db, save/load functions, and migration logic could become a dedicated persistence module with a clean repository interface, making it easier to swap storage backends or add testing mocks.\"}]\n\n### Area: agentic-engine\nThe agentic-engine is a lightweight, framework-agnostic autonomous AI workflow engine. It follows a layered architecture with clear separation: OpenRouterClient handles external API communication with retry logic; runner.py orchestrates multi-layer workflows with session state management; loop.py implements both ReAct and native tool-calling agentic patterns; tool_executor.py provides defensive JSON parsing and safe tool dispatch; and knowledge.py manages content discovery and prompt assembly. The engine uses only stdlib plus Jinja2, supports JSON-defined workflows, and provides both programmatic and template-driven interfaces.\nCross-area refs: [\"imports jinja2 from external package (PyPI)\", \"references agentic.tools module (agentic-tools area) in README examples\", \"references agentic/workflows/ directory (agentic-docs-and-workflows area) in README\", \"references agentic/skills/ directory (agentic-docs-and-workflows area) in README\", \"references rules/docs/ directory (agentic-docs-and-workflows area) in README\"]\nSuggested splits: []\n\n### Area: claude-config-and-rules\nThis area contains project-level Claude Code configuration that governs how AI agents interact with the codebase. It establishes a rules-based governance system with design invariants (no silent file destruction, mandatory SQLite persistence), testing conventions (decentralized test plans in .claude/tests/, pytest for code), and bug-fixing discipline (root-cause analysis, no defensive suppression). Two skills are defined: code-documenter for generating module documentation rules, and code-search for AST-based code navigation using jcodemunch. The Spark configuration orchestrates multi-model workflows across planner, explorer, mapper, and writer roles using OpenRouter. The architecture follows a hierarchical rules pattern where RULES_INDEX.md serves as the central registry, with specialized rule files for invariants, testing, and bug-fixing forming the governance layer.\nCross-area refs: [\"references file_merger.py from invariants.md (MergeEngine.execute_merge, save_item_resolution)\", \"references restore_deleted_files.ps1 from invariants.md (PowerShell recovery script)\", \"references CLAUDE.md from code-documenter/SKILL.md (critical flows documentation)\", \"references jcodemunch_mcp package from code-search/SKILL.md (external code indexing tool)\", \"references tests/ directory from testing.md (actual test code location)\", \"references .code-index/ directory from code-search/SKILL.md (AST index location)\"]\nSuggested splits: []\n\n### Area: agentic-tools\nThis area implements a set of filesystem and code search tools for the agentic engine. It follows a consistent pattern where each tool is a standalone module with an `execute()` function that accepts parameters plus a `_base_dir` for security sandboxing. All tools return JSON strings for easy integration with the agentic workflow system. The tools include file reading/writing, directory listing, file tree generation, and regex-based code search, with built-in path validation to prevent directory traversal attacks. The definitions.json provides the schema that the agentic engine uses to discover and invoke these tools.\nCross-area refs: []\nSuggested splits: []\n\n### Area: web-templates\nThe web-templates area provides a complete Jinja2 template suite for the Flask-based File Recovery Merger application. It uses Bootstrap 5 with a dark theme and implements a multi-page workflow: setup wizard, file browser with tree navigation, inventory table, conflict resolution (list and detail views), interactive merge editor with hunk-level control, coverage dashboard, and real-time progress pages using Server-Sent Events. The templates follow a consistent inheritance pattern from base.html, share common CSS for diff visualization and status badges, and implement rich client-side JavaScript for keyboard navigation, AJAX resolution, and dynamic content loading.\nCross-area refs: [\"imports Flask route handlers from core-application (/setup, /browse, /inventory, /conflicts, /conflict/*, /merge/*, /resolve*, /execute, /api/*, /scan-events, /merge-events, /extract-events, /log, /export-log, /extract-history)\", \"uses Bootstrap 5.3.3 CSS and JS from CDN\", \"uses Jinja2 template engine features (extends, block, for, if, with, tojson filter)\"]\nSuggested splits: []\n\n## Previous Relationship Map\n\n```json\n{\n  \"edges\": [\n    {\n      \"from_area\": \"web-templates\",\n      \"to_area\": \"core-application\",\n      \"type\": \"calls\",\n      \"details\"