    "content": "## Your Area Assignment\n\n**Area:** agentic-engine\n**Description:** Lightweight autonomous AI workflow engine: OpenRouterClient for LLM API communication, runner.py for multi-layer workflow orchestration, loop.py for ReAct and native tool-calling patterns, tool_executor.py for safe tool dispatch, and knowledge.py for skill/knowledge discovery and prompt assembly.\n**File patterns:** [\"agentic/engine/__init__.py\", \"agentic/engine/knowledge.py\", \"agentic/engine/loop.py\", \"agentic/engine/openrouter.py\", \"agentic/engine/runner.py\", \"agentic/engine/tool_executor.py\"]\n\n## Plan Summary\n\nAreas in the plan:\n- core-application: Monolithic Flask application (file_merger.py) implementing the complete file recovery and merge tool: data models (FileVersion, MergeItem, SourceConfig), core services (FileScanner, MergeEngine, EditorHistoryExtractor, RecoveryAdvisor), SQLite persistence with WAL mode, and Flask route controllers with SSE-based progress streaming.\n- web-templates: Jinja2 template suite for the Flask UI: Bootstrap 5 dark-themed pages covering the full workflow (setup wizard, file browser, inventory, conflict resolution, merge editor, coverage dashboard, history extraction) with SSE progress pages and rich client-side JavaScript.\n- agentic-engine: Lightweight autonomous AI workflow engine: OpenRouterClient for LLM API communication, runner.py for multi-layer workflow orchestration, loop.py for ReAct and native tool-calling patterns, tool_executor.py for safe tool dispatch, and knowledge.py for skill/knowledge discovery and prompt assembly.\n- agentic-tools: Filesystem and code search tools for the agentic engine: each module exposes an execute() function with _base_dir sandboxing, returning JSON strings. Includes read_file, write_file, list_directory, get_file_tree, and search_code, plus definitions.json schema for tool discovery.\n- agentic-docs-and-workflows: Documentation, workflow definitions, and skill templates for the agentic engine: reference docs covering architecture, JSON definitions, knowledge system, skills, and workflows; example workflow JSON; example skill template; and the agentic README as the developer entry point.\n- claude-config-and-rules: Claude Code project configuration and AI governance: RULES_INDEX.md as central registry, rule files for invariants/testing/bug-fixing, Claude skills (code-documenter, code-search), Spark multi-model workflow configuration, and local settings. Governs how AI agents interact with the codebase.\n- project-root-and-scripts: Top-level project metadata, entry-point documentation, and utility scripts: CLAUDE.md as the project overview and rule discovery entry point, PowerShell standalone recovery script, version marker, git configuration, and operational artifacts.\n- code-index-generated: Auto-generated AST code index files produced by jcodemunch for code search functionality. These are derived artifacts, not source code.\n\n## Instructions\n\nAnalyze all files matching your area's patterns. Return a JSON report with `area`, `files`, `area_summary`, `cross_area_refs`, and optionally `suggested_splits`."
