ory.py** (utility): Lists directory entries with type indicators (file/dir), supports optional recursive listing up to depth 3, and enforces path sandboxing to prevent directory traversal attacks.\n    Exports: [\"execute(path, recursive, _base_dir, **kwargs) -> str\"]\n    Imports from: [\"json (stdlib)\", \"os (stdlib)\"]\n  - **agentic/tools/read_file.py** (utility): Reads file contents with optional line range selection, converts 1-based line numbers to 0-based internally, and returns JSON with content and metadata.\n    Exports: [\"execute(path, start_line, end_line, _base_dir, **kwargs) -> str\"]\n    Imports from: [\"json (stdlib)\", \"os (stdlib)\"]\n  - **agentic/tools/search_code.py** (utility): Performs regex search across files in a directory tree with file pattern filtering, directory pruning, binary file skipping, and result truncation at 100 matches.\n    Exports: [\"execute(pattern, file_pattern, path, _base_dir, **kwargs) -> str\"]\n    Imports from: [\"fnmatch (stdlib)\", \"json (stdlib)\", \"os (stdlib)\", \"re (stdlib)\"]\n  - **agentic/tools/write_file.py** (utility): Writes content to a file with automatic parent directory creation, path sandboxing enforcement, and returns JSON with write confirmation and line count.\n    Exports: [\"execute(path, content, _base_dir, **kwargs) -> str\"]\n    Imports from: [\"json (stdlib)\", \"os (stdlib)\"]\n\n### Area: claude-config-and-rules\n\n**Summary:** \n\n**Cross-area references:** []\n\n**Files:**\n\n\n### Area: agentic-docs-and-workflows\n\n**Summary:** This area contains the complete documentation suite and templates for the agentic workflow engine. The documentation follows a self-contained design principle where each doc covers a specific concern (architecture, JSON definitions, knowledge system, skills, workflows) without requiring source code inspection. The area includes YAML-frontmatter-based skill templates and JSON workflow definitions that demonstrate the engine's capabilities. The architectural pattern is documentation-as-configuration: markdown files with structured frontmatter drive runtime behavior (skill discovery, knowledge injection) while serving as human-readable reference.\n\n**Cross-area references:** [\"references agentic.engine.run_workflow from agentic-engine\", \"references agentic.engine.OpenRouterClient from agentic-engine\", \"references agentic.tools.read_file from agentic-tools\", \"references agentic.tools.search_code from agentic-tools\", \"references agentic.tools.list_directory from agentic-tools\", \"references agentic.tools.write_file from agentic-tools\", \"references agentic.tools.get_file_tree from agentic-tools\", \"references agentic.engine.knowledge.resolve_knowledge from agentic-engine\", \"references agentic.engine.knowledge.discover_skills from agentic-engine\", \"references agentic.engine.runner.LightweightWorkflowSession from agentic-engine\", \"references agentic.tools.definitions.json from agentic-tools\"]\n\n**Files:**\n  - **agentic/README.md** (documentation): Developer entry point for the agentic engine providing quick start guide, workflow/tool/skill creation examples, and documentation index.\n    Exports: []\n    Imports from: []\n  - **agentic/rules/docs/agentic-overview.md** (documentation): High-level architecture overview with directory layout, execution model, and capability routing table directing readers to specific docs.\n    Exports: []\n    Imports from: []\n  - **agentic/rules/docs/json-definitions.md** (documentation): Comprehensive reference for creating workflows and tools via JSON: layer types (prompt, agentic_loop, smart_template, tool), prompt processing pipeline, and tool definitions format.\n    Exports: []\n    Imports from: []\n  - **agentic/rules/docs/knowledge-system.md** (documentation): Documents the knowledge injection system: rules (full content), knowledge_set (summaries), skills (summaries), YAML frontmatter standard, and resolution pipeline.\n    Exports: []\n    Imports from: []\n  - **agentic/rules/docs/skills.md** (documentation): Skills architecture guide covering SKILL.md format, folder structure, JSON skill definitions, discovery mechanism, and sub-agent definitions.\n    Exports: []\n    Imports from: []\n  - **agentic/rules/docs/workflows.md** (documentation): Workflow engine documentation covering LightweightWorkflowSession, layer processing pipeline, agentic loop modes (ReAct/native), and execution flow.\n    Exports: []\n    Imports from: []\n  - **agentic/skills/example-skill/SKILL.md** (template): Example skill template demonstrating the SKILL.md format with YAML frontmatter (name, description, allowed-tools) and phased instruction structure.\n    Exports: []\n    Imports from: []\n  - **agentic/workflows/example_workflow.json** (config): Example JSON workflow with two layers: an agentic_loop for file analysis and a smart_template for formatting output using Jinja2 variables.\n    Exports: []\n    Imports from: []\n\n### Area: project-root-and-scripts\n\n**Summary:** This area serves as the project's entry point and operational metadata layer. CLAUDE.md acts as the central discovery hub for AI agents, implementing a decentralized documentation protocol that directs agents to module-specific RULES_INDEX.md files. The PowerShell script provides a standalone command-line alternative to the web UI for file recovery operations. The sessions/ directory acts as the runtime persistence layer for SQLite databases. Together these files establish project identity, operational boundaries, and multi-modal access (web UI vs CLI) to the file recovery functionality.\n\n**Cross-area references:** [\"restore_deleted_files.ps1 references EditorHistoryExtractor logic from core-application (file_merger.py)\", \"CLAUDE.md documents FileScanner, MergeEngine, EditorHistoryExtractor classes from core-application\", \"CLAUDE.md references templates/ directory from web-templates area\", \"sessions/ directory is used by SQLite persistence layer in core-application (file_merger.py)\", \"CLAUDE.md references .claude/rules/ from claude-config-and-rules area\", \"CLAUDE.md references agentic/ documentation from agentic-docs-and-workflows area\"]\n\n**Files:**\n  - **CLAUDE.md** (entry-point): Primary project documentation and AI agent entry point describing Guanine (CodeEdit) — a multi-source file recovery and merge tool with Flask web UI, including architecture overview, directory layout, design invariants, and rule/skill discovery protocol.\n    Exports: []\n    Imports from: []\n  - **commands.txt** (config): Session resume notes containing Claude CLI command and Python virtual environment activation instructions for the file-recovery-merger-tool session.\n    Exports: []\n    Imports from: []\n  - **restore_deleted_files.ps1** (script): Standalone PowerShell script for recovering deleted files from editor local history (Windsurf, VS Code, Cursor) without requiring the web UI; supports dry-run, force overwrite, exclude filters, and cross-editor history path detection.\n    Exports: [\"Convert-UriToPath(uri) -> string\", \"Convert-ToDestinationPath(originalPath) -> string\"]\n    Imports from: []\n  - **0.12.0** (asset): Version marker file containing pip output artifact indicating pathspec package version 1.0.4 is installed.\n    Exports: []\n    Imports from: []\n  - **.gitignore** (config): Git ignore rules excluding sessions directory, merger config/state files, merge logs, and Python cache files.\n    Exports: []\n    Imports from: []\n  - **sessions/** (utility): Empty runtime directory for per-session SQLite database files used by the Flask application for persistence.\n    Exports: []\n    Imports from: []\n\n### Area: core-application\n\n**Summary:** The core-application area consists of a single monolithic Python file that implements the complete file recovery and merge tool. It follows a layered architecture within the single file: data models (FileVersion, MergeItem, SourceConfig) at the bottom, core services (FileScanner, MergeEngine, EditorHistoryExtractor, RecoveryAdvisor) in the middle, SQLite persistence layer with WAL mode for session management, and Flask route controllers at the top. The application uses Server-Sent Events (SSE) for real-time progress streaming during long-running operations like file scanning and merging. Notable technical decisions include: thread-local SQLite connections to avoid cross-thread object issues, automatic migration from legacy JSON files to SQLite, specialized handling for editor history directories (Windsurf/VS Code/Cursor), and content normalization for intelligent conflict detection beyond simple hash comparison.\n\n**Cross-area references:** [\"imports render_template, request, redirect, url_for, jsonify, Response, stream_with_context, flash from flask (external dependency)\", \"imports Markup from markupsafe (external dependency via Flask)\", \"references templates: setup.html, scan_progress.html, inventory.html, conflicts.html, conflict_detail.html, merge_progress.html, log.html, browse.html, _file_detail.html, merge_editor.html, coverage.html, extract_history.html, extract_progress.html (web-templates area)\", \"writes to sessions/ directory for SQLite databases (cross-area with project-root-and-scripts)\", \"reads/writes editor history from APPDATA/LOCALAPPDATA (external system paths)\"]\n\n**Files:**\n  - **file_merger.py** (entry-point): A monolithic Flask application (~2861 lines) implementing a complete file recovery and merge tool with multi-source file scanning, conflict detection, interactive merge editing, SQLite persistence with WAL mode, and SSE-based progress streaming. Includes specialized support for extracting files from Windsurf/VS Code/Cursor editor history directories.\n    Exports: [\"FileVersion(source_name, source_root, absolute_path, relative_path, file_size, modified_time, created_time, sha256, line_count, is_binary) -> dataclass\", \"MergeItem(relative_path, versions, category, selected_index, resolved) -> dataclass\", \"SourceConfig(name, path, priority) -> dataclass\", \"FileScanner(ignore_patterns) -> class\", \"MergeEngine() -> class\", \"RecoveryAdvisor() -> class\", \"EditorHistoryExtractor(project_folder, progress_queue) -> class\", \"generate_side_by_side_diff(version_a, version_b, context_lines) -> list\", \"list_sessions() -> list\", \"get_active_session_id() -> str\", \"set_active_session(session_id) -> None\", \"save_session_meta(session_id, session_name) -> None\", \"save_config(sources, target_dir, ignore_patterns) -> None\", \"load_config(session_id) -> dict\", \"save_inventory_state(inventory) -> None\", \"save_item_resolution(relative_path, selected_index, resolved) -> None\", \"save_batch_resolutions(updates) -> None\", \"load_inventory_state(session_id) -> dict\", \"delete_session(session_id) -> None\", \"app -> Flask application instance\", \"state -> dict (global application state)\"]\n    Imports from: [\"os (stdlib)\", \"sys (stdlib)\", \"hashlib (stdlib)\", \"json (stdlib)\", \"difflib (stdlib)\", \"threading (stdlib)\", \"fnmatch (stdlib)\", \"shutil (stdlib)\", \"time (stdlib)\", \"queue (stdlib)\", \"re (stdlib)\", \"sqlite3 (stdlib)\", \"datetime.datetime (stdlib)\", \"pathlib.Path (stdlib)\", \"dataclasses.dataclass, field, asdict (stdlib)\", \"typing.Optional (stdlib)\", \"urllib.parse.unquote (stdlib)\", \"concurrent.futures.ThreadPoolExecutor, as_completed (stdlib)\", \"flask.Flask, render_template, request, redirect, url_for, jsonify, Response, stream_with_context, flash (external: Flask)\", \"markupsafe.Markup (external: markupsafe/Flask)\"]\n\n### Area: web-templates\n\n**Summary:** The web-templates area provides a complete Jinja2 template suite for the Flask-based File Recovery Merger application. It implements a Bootstrap 5 dark-themed UI covering the full workflow: setup wizard with session management, interactive file browser with tree navigation and inline conflict resolution, inventory and conflict list views, advanced hunk-based merge editor, coverage dashboard, editor history extraction, and real-time progress pages using Server-Sent Events. The templates follow a consistent inheritance pattern from base.html, use AJAX extensively for dynamic content, and include rich client-side JavaScript for keyboard navigation, real-time updates, and interactive merge operations.\n\n**Cross-area references:** [\"imports get_flashed_messages, request from Flask (core-application)\", \"imports API endpoints from core-application: /api/browse-tree, /api/file-detail/*, /api/file-content/*, /api/save-merge, /api/coverage-files/*\", \"imports SSE endpoints from core-application: /scan-events, /merge-events, /extract-events\", \"imports POST endpoints from core-application: /setup, /execute, /resolve, /resolve-toggle, /resolve-accept-defaults, /resolve-all-latest, /extract-history\", \"imports GET endpoints from core-application: /browse, /inventory, /conflicts, /conflict/*, /merge/*, /coverage, /log, /setup, /extract-history, /export-log, /session/*\"]\n\n**Files:**\n  - **templates/base.html** (template): Base layout template providing the common HTML structure, Bootstrap 5 dark-themed styling, navigation bar, and flash message handling for all pages.\n    Exports: [\"base layout template with Bootstrap 5 dark theme\", \"navigation bar\", \"flash message handling\", \"CSS block hooks (extra_css, extra_js)\"]\n    Imports from: [\"Flask (get_flashed_messages, request)\"]\n  - **templates/setup.html** (template): Setup wizard page for configuring source directories, target directory, ignore patterns, and managing multiple scanning sessions.\n    Exports: [\"session management UI\", \"source configuration form\", \"dynamic source entry addition/removal\"]\n    Imports from: [\"base.html (extends)\", \"Flask template variables: has_saved_state, saved_stats, current_session, config_saved_at, all_sessions, sources, target_dir, project_filter, ignore_patterns\"]\n  - **templates/browse.html** (template): Main file browser with resizable sidebar tree view, inline conflict resolution, version selection, and side-by-side diff viewing with keyboard navigation.\n    Exports: [\"interactive file tree browser\", \"AJAX file detail loading\", \"conflict resolution UI\", \"keyboard navigation\", \"filtering by category\"]\n    Imports from: [\"base.html (extends)\", \"API endpoints: /api/browse-tree, /api/file-detail/*, /resolve, /resolve-toggle, /resolve-accept-defaults\", \"POST endpoints: /execute\"]\n  - **templates/inventory.html** (template): Tabular inventory view with pagination, sorting, filtering, and bulk action buttons for executing merges.\n    Exports: [\"paginated file inventory table\", \"sortable columns\", \"filter tabs\", \"action buttons for merge execution\"]\n    Imports from: [\"base.html (extends)\", \"Flask template variables: stats, items, filter_type, search, sort_by, sort_dir, page, total_pages, total_items\", \"POST endpoint: /execute\"]\n  - **templates/conflicts.html** (template): Conflict resolution overview page showing progress, listing all conflicts with status, and providing bulk auto-resolution.\n    Exports: [\"conflict list with progress bar\", \"auto-resolve all button\", \"completion detection\"]\n    Imports from: [\"base.html (extends)\", \"Flask template variables: resolved, total, items\", \"POST endpoint: /resolve-all-latest\", \"GET endpoint: /conflict/*\"]\n  - **templates/conflict_detail.html** (template): Detailed conflict resolution page showing version metadata cards, selectable diff views, and version selection with navigation.\n    Exports: [\"version comparison cards\", \"side-by-side diff view\", \"unified diff view\", \"version selection form\", \"keyboard shortcuts\"]\n    Imports from: [\"base.html (extends)\", \"Flask template variables: filepath, prev_path, next_path, current_idx, total_conflicts, resolved, versions, diff_a_idx, diff_b_idx, side_by_side, diff_lines\", \"POST endpoint: /resolve\", \"GET endpoint: /merge/*\"]\n  - **templates/merge_editor.html** (template): Advanced merge editor allowing per-hunk resolution with visual diff, bulk actions, and manual text editing mode for fine-tuning results.\n    Exports: [\"interactive hunk-based merge editor\", \"hunk picking (left/right/both/neither)\", \"edit mode with text editor\", \"live preview\", \"keyboard shortcuts\"]\n    Imports from: [\"base.html (extends)\", \"Flask template variables: filepath, versions, idx_a, idx_b, source_a, source_b, hunks\", \"API endpoint: /api/save-merge\"]\n  - **templates/coverage.html** (template): Coverage dashboard showing per-source contribution breakdown with visual progress bars and expandable file listings.\n    Exports: [\"source coverage visualization\", \"progress bars per source\", \"file categorization breakdown\", \"lazy-loaded file lists\"]\n    Imports from: [\"base.html (extends)\", \"Flask template variables: stats, coverage\", \"API endpoint: /api/coverage-files/*\"]\n  - **templates/extract_history.html** (template): Configuration page for extracting files from Windsurf/VS Code/Cursor editor history with detected sources and extraction settings.\n    Exports: [\"editor history source detection display\", \"extraction configuration form\"]\n    Imports from: [\"base.html (extends)\", \"Flask template variables: sources\", \"POST endpoint: /extract-history\"]\n  - **templates/scan_progress.html** (template): Progress page for file scanning operation using SSE to display real-time progress, per-source counts, and completion statistics.\n    Exports: [\"SSE progress streaming UI\", \"real-time scan statistics\", \"completion redirect\"]\n    Imports from: [\"base.html (extends)\", \"SSE endpoint: /scan-events\", \"GET endpoints: /inventory, /conflicts\"]\n  - **templates/merge_progress.html** (template): Progress page for merge execution showing real-time file copy progress, categorized counters, and detailed completion report.\n    Exports: [\"SSE merge progress UI\", \"file operation counters\", \"completion report with file lists\"]\n    Imports from: [\"base.html (extends)\", \"SSE endpoint: /merge-events\", \"GET endpoints: /log, /browse, /conflicts\"]\n  - **templates/extract_progress.html** (template): Progress page for editor history extraction with scanning and copying phases, message log, and completion statistics.\n    Exports: [\"SSE extraction progress UI\", \"multi-stage progress (scanning/copying)\", \"completion stats\"]\n    Imports from: [\"base.html (extends)\", \"SSE endpoint: /extract-events\", \"GET endpoints: /setup, /extract-history\"]\n  - **templates/log.html** (template): Activity log page showing merge results, action history with filtering, and recovery suggestions with command references.\n    Exports: [\"action log table\", \"merge result display\", \"recovery suggestions panel\", \"JSON export\"]\n    Imports from: [\"base.html (extends)\", \"Flask template variables: merge_result, log_path, log_entries, suggestions\", \"GET endpoint: /export-log\"]\n  - **templates/_file_detail.html** (template): Partial template rendered via AJAX for the file detail panel in the browse view, showing version metadata, diff views, and resolution controls.\n    Exports: [\"AJAX-loaded file detail panel\", \"version comparison cards\", \"side-by-side diff\", \"quick resolution buttons\"]\n    Imports from: [\"Flask template variables: filepath, item, versions, diff_a_idx, diff_b_idx, side_by_side\", \"API endpoints: /api/file-content/*, /api/file-detail/*\", \"POST endpoint: /resolve\"]\n\n### Area: agentic-engine\n\n**Summary:** The agentic-engine is a lightweight autonomous AI workflow engine implementing a layered architecture for LLM-powered automation. It provides a multi-layer workflow runner (runner.py) that orchestrates sequential processing steps, dual-mode agentic loops (loop.py) supporting both ReAct text-parsing and native OpenAI function-calling patterns, a stdlib-only OpenRouter HTTP client (openrouter.py) with retry logic, safe tool execution (tool_executor.py) with signature filtering, and a knowledge resolution system (knowledge.py) for discovering and assembling rules/skills into prompts. The engine uses Jinja2 templating, session-based state management, and XML-wrapped knowledge injection to create flexible, composable AI workflows without external dependencies beyond jinja2.\n\n**Cross-area references:** [\"imports jinja2 from external package (runner.py)\", \"imports execute_tool_call from tool_executor (loop.py)\", \"imports OpenRouterClient from openrouter (runner.py, loop.py)\", \"imports process_agentic_loop, process_agentic_loop_native from loop (runner.py)\", \"imports resolve_knowledge from knowledge (runner.py)\"]\n\n**Files:**\n  - **agentic/engine/__init__.py** (entry-point): Public API entry point that re-exports all key components from the agentic engine submodules, serving as the primary interface for consumers.\n    Exports: [\"OpenRouterClient\", \"LightweightWorkflowSession\", \"process_layer(layer_def, session, client, tool_registry) -> dict\", \"run_workflow(workflow_json, client, tool_registry, input_data) -> dict\", \"execute_tool_call(available_tools, tool_name, tool_args) -> str\", \"extract_json(response) -> dict | None\", \"parse_tool_args(raw_args) -> dict\", \"process_agentic_loop(layer_def, session, client, tool_registry, knowledge) -> dict\", \"process_agentic_loop_native(layer_def, session, client, tool_registry, knowledge) -> dict\", \"summarize_loop(chat_history, client, model) -> str\", \"extract_frontmatter(file_path) -> dict\", \"resolve_knowledge(rules, skills, knowledge_set, base_dir) -> dict\", \"build_rules_index(file_paths) -> str\", \"build_skills_index(metadata) -> str\", \"discover_skills(base_dir) -> list[dict]\"]\n    Imports from: [\"OpenRouterClient from .openrouter\", \"LightweightWorkflowSession, process_layer, run_workflow from .runner\", \"execute_tool_call, extract_json, parse_tool_args from .tool_executor\", \"process_agentic_loop, process_agentic_loop_native, summarize_loop from .loop\", \"extract_frontmatter, resolve_knowledge, build_rules_index, build_skills_index, discover_skills from .knowledge\"]\n  - **agentic/engine/knowledge.py** (service): Knowledge resolution system that discovers, parses, and assembles rules and skills from markdown files for injection into LLM prompts.\n    Exports: [\"extract_frontmatter(file_path) -> dict\", \"_parse_frontmatter_block(text) -> dict | None\", \"_heuristic_meta(text, file_path) -> dict\", \"build_rules_index(file_paths) -> str\", \"build_skills_index(metadata) -> str\", \"discover_skills(base_dir) -> list[dict]\", \"resolve_knowledge(rules, skills, knowledge_set, base_dir) -> dict\"]\n    Imports from: [\"json (stdlib)\", \"logging (stdlib)\", \"os (stdlib)\", \"re (stdlib)\", \"pathlib.Path (stdlib)\", \"typing.Any (stdlib)\"]\n  - **agentic/engine/loop.py** (controller): Implements dual-mode agentic loops: ReAct text-parsing and native tool-calling, with shared system message assembly and automatic conversation summarization.\n    Exports: [\"process_agentic_loop(layer_def, session, client, tool_registry, knowledge) -> dict\", \"process_agentic_loop_native(layer_def, session, client, tool_registry, knowledge) -> dict\", \"summarize_loop(chat_history, client, model) -> str\", \"_build_system_message(layer_def, knowledge, tool_descriptions, mode) -> str\", \"_tool_descriptions_text(tool_registry) -> str\", \"_tool_schemas(tool_registry) -> list[dict]\", \"_safe_summarize(chat_history, client, model) -> str\", \"_format_transcript(messages) -> str\"]\n    Imports from: [\"execute_tool_call from .tool_executor\", \"json (stdlib)\", \"logging (stdlib)\", \"re (stdlib)\", \"typing.Any (stdlib)\"]\n  - **agentic/engine/openrouter.py** (service): Lightweight stdlib-only HTTP client for OpenRouter API with automatic retry, exponential backoff, and normalized response format.\n    Exports: [\"OpenRouterClient\", \"OpenRouterError\", \"_MAX_RETRIES\", \"_BACKOFF_SECONDS\"]\n    Imports from: [\"json (stdlib)\", \"logging (stdlib)\", \"time (stdlib)\", \"urllib.error (stdlib)\", \"urllib.request (stdlib)\", \"typing.Any (stdlib)\"]\n  - **agentic/engine/runner.py** (controller): Multi-layer workflow orchestrator that manages session state, processes different layer types (prompt, agentic loop, template, tool), and chains outputs between layers.\n    Exports: [\"LightweightWorkflowSession\", \"process_layer(layer_def, session, client, tool_registry) -> dict\", \"run_workflow(workflow_json, client, tool_registry, input_data) -> dict\", \"_resolve_placeholders(text, session) -> str\", \"_render_jinja(template_str, context) -> str\", \"_process_prompt(layer_def, session, client) -> dict\", \"_process_smart_template(layer_def, session) -> dict\", \"_process_tool(layer_def, session, tool_registry) -> dict\"]\n    Imports from: [\"OpenRouterClient from .openrouter\", \"process_agentic_loop, process_agentic_loop_native from .loop\", \"resolve_knowledge from .knowledge\", \"jinja2 (external)\", \"copy (stdlib)\", \"json (stdlib)\", \"logging (stdlib)\", \"re (stdlib)\", \"typing.Any (stdlib)\"]\n  - **agentic/engine/tool_executor.py** (service): Safe tool execution utilities that extract structured data from LLM responses and dispatch tool calls with signature-aware argument filtering.\n    Exports: [\"extract_json(response) -> dict | None\", \"parse_tool_args(raw_args) -> dict\", \"execute_tool_call(available_tools, tool_name, tool_args) -> str\", \"_extract_braced_json(text) -> dict | None\", \"_filter_args(func, args) -> dict\"]\n    Imports from: [\"inspect (stdlib)\", \"json (stdlib)\", \"logging (stdlib)\", \"re (stdlib)\", \"typing.Any (stdlib)\"]\n\n\n## Current Area Plan\n\n```json\n[\n  {\n    \"name\": \"core-application\",\n    \"description\": \"Monolithic Flask application (file_merger.py) implementing the complete file recovery and merge tool: data models (FileVersion, MergeItem, 