u2014 Update single item resolution (instant)\",\n        \"_restore_session() -> None \\u2014 Restore active session on startup with legacy migration\",\n        \"setup() -> Response \\u2014 Flask route: configuration and scan initiation\",\n        \"scan_events() -> Response \\u2014 Flask route: SSE endpoint for scan progress streaming\",\n        \"inventory() -> Response \\u2014 Flask route: file inventory listing with filtering/pagination\",\n        \"conflict_detail(filepath) -> Response \\u2014 Flask route: conflict resolution detail page\",\n        \"resolve() -> Response \\u2014 Flask route: resolve conflict POST handler\",\n        \"execute() -> Response \\u2014 Flask route: execute merge POST handler\",\n        \"merge_events() -> Response \\u2014 Flask route: SSE endpoint for merge progress streaming\",\n        \"merge_editor(filepath) -> Response \\u2014 Flask route: interactive merge editor\",\n        \"save_merge() -> Response \\u2014 Flask route: save manually merged file\",\n        \"browse_tree_api() -> Response \\u2014 Flask route: JSON API for file browser tree\",\n        \"file_detail_api(filepath) -> Response \\u2014 Flask route: HTML fragment for file detail panel\",\n        \"coverage_page() -> Response \\u2014 Flask route: source coverage dashboard\",\n        \"_generate_merge_hunks(version_a, version_b) -> list \\u2014 Generate merge hunks for interactive editor\"\n      ],\n      \"patterns\": [\n        \"Monolithic architecture \\u2014 Single file contains models, services, persistence, and web layer\",\n        \"Dataclass models \\u2014 Immutable data structures with serialization helpers (to_dict)\",\n        \"Service classes \\u2014 FileScanner, MergeEngine, RecoveryAdvisor, EditorHistoryExtractor encapsulate domain logic\",\n        \"ThreadPoolExecutor \\u2014 Concurrent file scanning and hashing for performance\",\n        \"Queue-based progress reporting \\u2014 Background operations report progress via queue for SSE streaming\",\n        \"SQLite with WAL mode \\u2014 Write-Ahead Logging for concurrent reads during background operations\",\n        \"Thread-local storage \\u2014 SQLite connections stored per-thread to avoid cross-thread object issues\",\n        \"Session-based persistence \\u2014 Each session has isolated SQLite database in sessions/<id>/ folder\",\n        \"Legacy migration \\u2014 Automatic migration from JSON flat files to SQLite structure\",\n        \"Server-Sent Events (SSE) \\u2014 Real-time progress streaming for scan, merge, and extract operations\",\n        \"Global state dictionary \\u2014 In-memory state management (not thread-safe for multi-process)\",\n        \"Template rendering \\u2014 Server-side Jinja2 rendering with Bootstrap 5 dark theme\",\n        \"RESTful API endpoints \\u2014 /api/* routes return JSON for client-side interactivity\",\n        \"Auto-categorization \\u2014 Files automatically categorized as unique, identical, or conflict based on hash/content comparison\",\n        \"Content normalization \\u2014 Line ending and trailing whitespace normalization for content comparison\"\n      ],\n      \"summary\": \"A monolithic Flask application (~2861 lines) implementing a complete file recovery and merge tool with multi-source file scanning, conflict detection, interactive merge editing, SQLite persistence with WAL mode, and SSE-based progress streaming. Includes specialized support for extracting files from Windsurf/VS Code/Cursor editor history directories.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"area_summary\": \"The core-application area consists of a single monolithic Python file that implements the complete file recovery and merge tool. It follows a layered architecture within the single file: data models (FileVersion, MergeItem, SourceConfig) at the bottom, core services (FileScanner, MergeEngine, EditorHistoryExtractor, RecoveryAdvisor) in the middle, SQLite persistence layer with WAL mode for session management, and Flask route controllers at the top. The application uses Server-Sent Events (SSE) for real-time progress streaming during long-running operations like file scanning and merging. Notable technical decisions include: thread-local SQLite connections to avoid cross-thread object issues, automatic migration from legacy JSON files to SQLite, specialized handling for editor history directories (Windsurf/VS Code/Cursor), and content normalization for intelligent conflict detection beyond simple hash comparison.\",\n  \"cross_area_refs\": [\n    \"imports render_template, request, redirect, url_for, jsonify, Response, stream_with_context, flash from flask (external dependency)\",\n    \"imports Markup from markupsafe (external dependency via Flask)\",\n    \"references templates: setup.html, scan_progress.html, inventory.html, conflicts.html, conflict_detail.html, merge_progress.html, log.html, browse.html, _file_detail.html, merge_editor.html, coverage.html, extract_history.html, extract_progress.html (web-templates area)\",\n    \"writes to sessions/ directory for SQLite databases (cross-area with project-root-and-scripts)\",\n    \"reads/writes editor history from APPDATA/LOCALAPPDATA (external system paths)\"\n  ],\n  \"suggested_splits\": [\n    {\n      \"suggestion\": \"Split into modular package structure\",\n      \"rationale\": \"The 2861-line monolithic file could be split into a proper Python package for better maintainability\",\n      \"proposed_structure\": [\n        \"models.py \\u2014 FileVersion, MergeItem, SourceConfig dataclasses\",\n        \"scanner.py \\u2014 FileScanner class with editor history detection\",\n        \"merge_engine.py \\u2014 MergeEngine class\",\n        \"history_extractor.py \\u2014 EditorHistoryExtractor class\",\n        \"advisor.py \\u2014 RecoveryAdvisor class\",\n        \"persistence.py \\u2014 SQLite session management functions\",\n        \"diff_utils.py \\u2014 Side-by-side diff and merge hunk generators\",\n        \"routes.py \\u2014 Flask route handlers\",\n        \"app.py \\u2014 Application factory and global state\"\n      ]\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n## Relationship Edges for This Area\n\n```json\n[\n  {\n    \"from_area\": \"web-templates\",\n    \"to_area\": \"core-application\",\n    \"type\": \"calls\",\n    \"details\": \"All templates consume Flask route endpoints: /api/browse-tree, /api/file-detail/*, /api/file-content/*, /api/save-merge, /api/coverage-files/*, /scan-events (SSE), /merge-events (SSE), /extract-events (SSE), /setup, /execute, /resolve, /resolve-toggle, /resolve-accept-defaults, /resolve-all-latest, /extract-history, /browse, /inventory, /conflicts, /conflict/*, /merge/*, /coverage, /log, /export-log, /session/*. Templates also use Flask context variables: get_flashed_messages, request, and numerous template variables passed from route handlers.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"from_area\": \"core-application\",\n    \"to_area\": \"web-templates\",\n    \"type\": \"calls\",\n    \"details\": \"file_merger.py calls render_template() for: setup.html, scan_progress.html, inventory.html, conflicts.html, conflict_detail.html, merge_progress.html, log.html, browse.html, _file_detail.html, merge_editor.html, coverage.html, extract_history.html, extract_progress.html\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"from_area\": \"core-application\",\n    \"to_area\": \"project-root-and-scripts\",\n    \"type\": \"calls\",\n    \"details\": \"file_merger.py writes SQLite databases to the sessions/ directory for persistence\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"from_area\": \"project-root-and-scripts\",\n    \"to_area\": \"core-application\",\n    \"type\": \"shares_types\",\n    \"details\": \"restore_deleted_files.ps1 reimplements EditorHistoryExtractor logic from file_merger.py; CLAUDE.md documents FileScanner, MergeEngine, EditorHistoryExtractor classes\"\n  }\n]\n```\n\n## Shared Types Involving This Area\n\n```json\n[\n  {\n    \"name\": \"Flask template context variables\",\n    \"defined_in\": \"core-application\",\n    \"used_in\": [\n 