        "arguments": "{\"path\":\".claude/rules/docs/project-root-and-scripts.md\",\"content\":\"# Guanine(CodeEdit) — Project Root and Scripts Documentation\\n> Auto-generated by Spark. Last updated: 2026-04-06\\n> Source area: project-root-and-scripts\\n\\n## Purpose\\nThis area serves as the project's entry point and operational metadata layer. `CLAUDE.md` is the central discovery hub for AI agents, implementing a decentralized documentation protocol that directs agents to module-specific `RULES_INDEX.md` files. `restore_deleted_files.ps1` provides a standalone CLI alternative to the web UI for file recovery from editor local history. The `sessions/` directory is the runtime persistence layer for per-session SQLite databases.\\n\\n## Data Flows\\n\\n- **AI agent discovery**: Agents read `CLAUDE.md` first, then follow the rule discovery protocol to load module-specific rules from `.claude/rules/` and `.claude/RULES_INDEX.md`.\\n- **CLI file recovery**: `restore_deleted_files.ps1` scans editor history directories (Windsurf, VS Code, Cursor), parses `entries.json` files, resolves backup files, and copies them to a destination folder — all without the Flask app.\\n- **Session persistence**: `core-application` (`file_merger.py`) writes per-session SQLite databases into `sessions/` at runtime.\\n\\n## Invariants Enforced\\n\\n- **No silent file destruction** (documented in CLAUDE.md, enforced in `restore_deleted_files.ps1` via confirmation prompt and `-Force` flag requirement).\\n- **Session persistence**: Session data must always be persisted to SQLite in `sessions/`, never held only in memory.\\n\\n## Definitions\\n\\n### Functions\\n| Function | File | Signature | Description |\\n|----------|------|-----------|-------------|\\n| `Convert-UriToPath` | `restore_deleted_files.ps1` | `(uri: string) -> string` | Converts `file://` URIs to Windows filesystem paths, unescaping percent-encoding and normalizing slashes |\\n| `Convert-ToDestinationPath` | `restore_deleted_files.ps1` | `(originalPath: string) -> string` | Maps original project paths to destination folder structure; returns original path if destination equals project folder |\\n| Main script logic | `restore_deleted_files.ps1` | CLI params: `-ProjectFolder`, `-DestinationFolder`, `-ExcludeFolder`, `-Hours`, `-DryRun`, `-Force`, `-show_all` | Scans 9 possible editor history paths, parses `entries.json`, resolves backup files via 3 methods (entry.id, entry.source URI, newest file), filters by project/time/exclusion, and restores with confirmation |\\n\\n### Files\\n| File | Role | Description |\\n|------|------|-------------|\\n| `CLAUDE.md` | Entry point / documentation hub | Project overview, architecture, directory layout, design invariants, rule discovery protocol, coding guidelines |\\n| `restore_deleted_files.ps1` | Standalone CLI script | PowerShell script for recovering deleted files from Windsurf/VS Code/Cursor local history |\\n| `commands.txt` | Session resume notes | Claude CLI resume command and venv activation instructions |\\n| `.gitignore` | Git config | Excludes `sessions/`, `.merger_config.json`, `.merger_state.json`, `merge_log_*.json`, `__pycache__/` |\\n| `sessions/` | Runtime data directory | Empty directory; per-session SQLite databases written here by `file_merger.py` |\\n| `0.12.0` | Version marker | Pip output artifact (pathspec 1.0.4) |\\n\\n## Module Dependencies\\n\\n### This area depends on:\\n| Area/Module | What is used | How |\\n|-------------|-------------|-----|\\n| `core-application` | `EditorHistoryExtractor` logic, `FileScanner`, `MergeEngine` class designs | `restore_deleted_files.ps1` reimplements editor history extraction logic; `CLAUDE.md` documents these classes |\\n| `claude-config-and-rules` | `.claude/rules/` directory | `CLAUDE.md` references it as part of the rule discovery protocol |\\n| `web-templates` | `templates/` directory | `CLAUDE.md` references it in the directory layout |\\n| `agentic-docs-and-workflows` | `agentic/`