        "arguments": "{\"path\":\".claude/rules/docs/web-templates.md\",\"content\":\"# Guanine(CodeEdit) — Web Templates Documentation\\n> Auto-generated by Spark. Last updated: 2026-04-06\\n> Source area: web-templates\\n\\n## Purpose\\nComplete Jinja2 template suite for the Flask-based File Recovery Merger application. Provides a Bootstrap 5 dark-themed UI covering the full workflow: setup wizard, interactive file browser with conflict resolution, inventory/conflict list views, hunk-based merge editor, coverage dashboard, editor history extraction, and real-time progress pages via Server-Sent Events.\\n\\n## Data Flows\\n- **Flask routes → templates**: Route handlers pass template variables (stats, items, versions, diffs, coverage data, log entries) via `render_template()`. All templates extend `base.html`.\\n- **Templates → Flask API (AJAX)**: `browse.html` and `_file_detail.html` call `/api/browse-tree`, `/api/file-detail/*`, `/api/file-content/*`, `/api/save-merge`, `/api/coverage-files/*` for dynamic content loading.\\n- **Templates → Flask SSE**: `scan_progress.html`, `merge_progress.html`, `extract_progress.html` consume Server-Sent Events from `/scan-events`, `/merge-events`, `/extract-events` respectively.\\n- **Templates → Flask POST**: Forms and JS functions POST to `/setup`, `/execute`, `/resolve`, `/resolve-toggle`, `/resolve-accept-defaults`, `/resolve-all-latest`, `/extract-history` for state mutations.\\n- **Flash messages**: `base.html` renders Flask flash messages with auto-dismiss via `get_flashed_messages()`.\\n\\n## Invariants Enforced\\n- All page templates extend `base.html` (except partial `_file_detail.html`).\\n- Jinja2 block contract: child templates fill `title`, `content`, and optionally `extra_css`/`extra_js`.\\n- Bootstrap 5 dark theme is applied globally via `data-bs-theme=\\\"dark\\\"` on `<html>`.\\n- Unsaved changes warning in `merge_editor.html` prevents accidental navigation.\\n\\n## Definitions\\n\\n### Templates\\n\\n| Template | File | Description |\\n|----------|------|-------------|\\n| Base Layout | `templates/base.html` | Common HTML structure, Bootstrap 5 dark theme, navbar, flash messages, CSS/JS block hooks |\\n| Setup Wizard | `templates/setup.html` | Source/target directory config, session CRUD, dynamic source entry add/remove |\\n| File Browser | `templates/browse.html` | Resizable sidebar tree, inline conflict resolution, keyboard navigation, AJAX detail loading |\\n| File Detail (partial) | `templates/_file_detail.html` | AJAX-injected panel with version cards, diff views, quick resolution buttons |\\n| Inventory | `templates/inventory.html` | Paginated/sortable/filterable table of all files with bulk action buttons |\\n| Conflicts List | `templates/conflicts.html` | Conflict progress bar, bulk auto-resolve, per-conflict navigation |\\n| Conflict Detail | `templates/conflict_detail.html` | Version comparison cards, side-by-side/unified diff, version selection, prev/next nav |\\n| Merge Editor | `templates/merge_editor.html` | Per-hunk picking (left/right/both/neither), text edit mode, live preview, save |\\n| Coverage Dashboard | `templates/coverage.html` | Per-source progress bars, file categorization, lazy-loaded file lists |\\n| Extract History | `templates/extract_history.html` | Editor history source detection, extraction config form |\\n| Scan Progress | `templates/scan_progress.html` | SSE real-time scan progress, per-source counts, completion stats |\\n| Merge Progress | `templates/merge_progress.html` | SSE merge progress, file operation counters, completion report |\\n| Extract Progress | `templates/extract_progress.html` | SSE extraction progress, multi-stage (scanning/copying), completion stats |\\n| Activity Log | `templates/log.html` | Merge result banner, reverse-chronological action log, recovery suggestions, JSON export |\\n\\n### Key Client-Side Functions\\n\\n| Function | Template | Description |\\n|----------|----------|-------------|\\n| `loadTree()` / `renderNode()` | `browse.html` | Fetches and recursively renders file tree via AJAX |\\n| `loadDetail()` / `navHunk()` | `browse.html`, `_file_detail.html` | Loads file detail panel, navigates between diff hunks |\\n| `pickVer()` / `toggleDone()` / `acceptAllDefaults()` | `browse.html` | Version selection, resolve/unresolve toggle, bulk accept defaults |\\n| `switchDiffPair()` / `selectVersion()` | `conflict_detail.html` | Changes compared version pair, visual version selection |\\n| `pickHunk()` / `pickAllLeft()` / `pickAllRight()` | `merge_editor.html` | Per-hunk and bulk hunk selection for merge |\\n| `buildMergedContent()` / `saveMerge()` | `merge_editor.html` | Constructs merged result from picks, persists via API |\\n| `toggleEditMode()` | `merge_editor.html` | Switches between hunk picker and free-text editor |\\n| `addSource()` / `removeSource()` | `setup.html` | Dynamic source directory entry management |\\n| `toggleFiles()` / `loadFiles()` | `coverage.html` | Expandable per-source file list via AJAX |\\n\\n## Module Dependencies\\n\\n### This area depends on:\\n| Area/Module | What is used | How |\\n|-------------|-------------|-----|\\n| core-application | Flask context (`get_flashed_messages`, `request`) | Template built-ins in `base.html` |\\n| core-application | Route endpoints (20+ GET/POST/API/SSE) | AJAX calls, form actions, SSE EventSource connections |\\n| core-application | Template variables (stats, items, versions, diffs, etc.) | Passed via `render_template()` from route handlers |\\n\\n### Other areas depend on this:\\n| Area/Module | What they use | How |\\n|-------------|--------------|-----|\\n| core-application | All 14 templates | `render_template()` calls in `file_merger.py` route handlers |\\n| project-root-and-scripts | `templates/` directory reference | Documented in `CLAUDE.md` project layout |\\n\\n## Impact Notes\\n- **core-application** is the sole consumer. Any change to template variable names (e.g., renaming `items` → `files`) 