        "arguments": "{\"path\":\".claude/rules/docs/agentic-docs-and-workflows.md\",\"content\":\"# Guanine(CodeEdit) — Agentic Docs and Workflows Documentation\\n> Auto-generated by Spark. Last updated: 2026-04-06\\n> Source area: agentic-docs-and-workflows\\n\\n## Purpose\\n\\nThis area contains the complete documentation suite, templates, and example definitions for the agentic workflow engine. It follows a **documentation-as-configuration** pattern: markdown files with structured YAML frontmatter drive runtime behavior (skill discovery, knowledge injection) while serving as human-readable reference. Each doc is self-contained — agents and developers should not need to read engine source code to create workflows, skills, or tools.\\n\\n## Data Flows\\n\\n- **Knowledge injection pipeline:** YAML-frontmatter markdown files → `extract_frontmatter()` → `build_rules_index()` / `build_skills_index()` → XML-tagged blocks (`<AVAILABLE_RULES>`, `<AVAILABLE_SKILLS>`) injected into agent system prompts\\n- **Skill discovery:** `SKILL.md` files in `agentic/skills/*/` and JSON files in `agentic/skill_definitions/` → `discover_skills()` → metadata list → `<AVAILABLE_SKILLS>` index\\n- **Workflow execution:** JSON workflow definitions → `run_workflow()` → `LightweightWorkflowSession` → sequential layer processing → accumulated context and outputs\\n- **Prompt processing:** Layer prompts → Jinja2 rendering (`{{ variable }}`) → placeholder replacement (`{PLO}`, `{OutputLayer-N}`) → LLM call or template output\\n\\n## Invariants Enforced\\n\\n- **Self-contained documentation:** All docs explicitly instruct readers not to open engine source code; the documented JSON structures and formats are the authoritative reference.\\n- **YAML frontmatter required fields:** Every rule/doc/skill markdown file must have `name` and `description` in its frontmatter. Fallback parsing extracts first `#` heading as name and first paragraph as description if frontmatter is missing.\\n- **Tool convention:** Every tool module must expose an `execute()` function returning a JSON string, accepting `_base_dir` and `**kwargs`.\\n- **Progressive disclosure:** `rules` are always fully injected; `knowledge_set` and `skills` show summaries only, with full content loaded on demand.\\n\\n## Definitions\\n\\n### Documentation Files\\n\\n| File | Purpose |\\n|------|---------|\\n| `agentic/README.md` | Developer entry point with quick start, workflow/tool/skill creation examples, and doc index |\\n| `agentic/rules/docs/agentic-overview.md` | Architecture overview, directory layout, execution model, capability routing table |\\n| `agentic/rules/docs/json-definitions.md` | Reference for JSON workflow structure, all 4 layer types, prompt processing pipeline, tool definitions format |\\n| `agentic/rules/docs/knowledge-system.md` | Knowledge injection: rules, knowledge_set, skills, YAML frontmatter standard, resolution pipeline |\\n| `agentic/rules/docs/skills.md` | Skills architecture: SKILL.md format, folder structure, JSON skill definitions, discovery, sub-agents |\\n| `agentic/rules/docs/workflows.md` | Workflow engine: LightweightWorkflowSession, layer processing, agentic loop modes, execution flow |\\n\\n### Templates and Examples\\n\\n| File | Purpose |\\n|------|---------|\\n| `agentic/skills/example-skill/SKILL.md` | Example skill template with YAML frontmatter (`name`, `description`, `allowed-tools`) and phased instructions |\\n| `agentic/workflows/example_workflow.json` | Example 2-layer workflow: `agentic_loop` for file analysis + `smart_template` for output formatting |\\n\\n### Key Runtime Concepts (documented here, implemented in agentic-engine)\\n\\n| Concept | Location | Description |\\n|---------|----------|-------------|\\n| `run_workflow()` | `agentic/engine/runner.py` | Main entry point; creates session, processes layers sequentially |\\n| `LightweightWorkflowSession` | `agentic/engine/runner.py` | In-memory session tracking context, chat_history, outputs, current_layer |\\n| `resolve_knowledge()` | `agentic/engine/knowledge.py` | Central resolver combining rules, knowledge_set, and skills into system prompt sections |\\n| `discover_skills()` | `agentic/engine/knowledge.py` | Scans `skills/*/SKILL.md` and `skill_definitions/*.json` for skill metadata |\\n| `OpenRouterClient` | `agentic/engine/openrouter.py` | HTTP client for LLM API calls (stdlib-only, no external HTTP deps) |\\n| `execute_tool_call()` | `agentic/engine/tool_executor.py` | Tool dispatch with JSON arg parsing and signature filtering |\\n\\n### Layer Types\\n\\n| Type | AI Call | Description |\\n|------|---------|-------------|\\n| `prompt` | Yes | Single LLM call with Jinja2-templated prompt |\\n| `agentic_loop` | Yes (iterative) | Autonomous agent with tools; ReAct or native function-calling mode |\\n| `smart_template` | No | Jinja2 template render against session context |\\n| `tool` | No | Direct tool execution by name |\\n\\n## Module Dependencies\\n\\n### This area depends on:\\n| Area/Module | What is used | How |\\n|-------------|-------------|-----|\\n| `agentic-engine` | `run_workflow`, `OpenRouterClient`, `LightweightWorkflowSession`, `resolve_knowledge`, `discover_skills` | Referenced in documentation as the runtime implementation of documented concepts |\\n| `agentic-tools` | `read_file`, `search_code`, `list_directory`, `write_file`, `get_file_tree`, `definitions.json` | Referenced in documentation as built-in tools and their JSON schema definitions |\\n\\n### Other areas depend on this:\\n| Area/Module | What they use | How |\\n|-------------|--------------|-----|\\n| `project-root-and-scripts` | `agentic/README.md` and `rules/docs/` index | `CLAUDE.md` references agentic documentation as part of the project documentation index |\\n\\n## Shared Types\\n\\n- **YAML frontmatter schema:** `name` (string, required), `description` (string, required), `allowed-tools` (list, skills only), `model` (string, sub-agents only), `tools` (list, sub-agent