        "arguments": "{\"path\":\".claude/rules/docs/agentic-engine.md\",\"content\":\"# Guanine(CodeEdit) — Agentic Engine Documentation\\n> Auto-generated by Spark. Last updated: 2026-04-06\\n> Source area: agentic-engine\\n\\n## Purpose\\nLightweight autonomous AI workflow engine implementing a layered architecture for LLM-powered automation. It orchestrates multi-layer workflows (prompt, agentic loop, template, tool), provides dual-mode agentic loops (ReAct text-parsing and native OpenAI function-calling), a stdlib-only OpenRouter HTTP client with retry logic, safe tool execution with signature filtering, and a knowledge resolution system for assembling rules/skills into prompts.\\n\\n## Data Flows\\n- **Workflow execution:** `run_workflow()` receives a workflow JSON dict → iterates layers → `process_layer()` dispatches by `layer_type` → each layer returns `{response, ...}` → session state accumulates → final `session.to_dict()` returned.\\n- **Agentic loop (ReAct):** System prompt assembled from layer def + knowledge → LLM called with stop token `<END_OF_ACTION>` → response parsed for `Action:`/`Answer:` patterns → tool calls dispatched via `execute_tool_call()` → observations appended → loop until answer or max iterations → `summarize_loop()` produces structured summary.\\n- **Agentic loop (native):** Same flow but uses OpenAI-format `tools` parameter → LLM returns `tool_calls` in response → executed and fed back as `role: tool` messages.\\n- **Knowledge resolution:** `resolve_knowledge()` reads rule files (full text), discovers skills from `skills/*/SKILL.md` and `skill_definitions/*.json`, builds XML-wrapped indexes → injected into system prompts via `_build_system_message()`.\\n- **Tool execution:** `execute_tool_call()` receives tool registry + name + args → `parse_tool_args()` normalizes string args → `_filter_args()` introspects function signature → filtered args passed to callable → result JSON-serialized.\\n\\n## Invariants Enforced\\n- `execute_tool_call` never raises — all errors are caught and returned as `{\\\"error\\\": \\\"...\\\"}` JSON strings.\\n- `_filter_args` strips arguments not present in the target function's signature (unless `**kwargs` is accepted), preventing injection of unexpected parameters.\\n- `OpenRouterClient._post` retries only on 429/5xx/URLError; 4xx client errors (except 429) raise immediately.\\n- `extract_json` and `parse_tool_args` return `None`/`{}` on failure rather than raising.\\n- `_safe_summarize` wraps `summarize_loop` to never propagate exceptions.\\n- Jinja2 rendering uses `BaseLoader` (no filesystem access) and returns the unprocessed template string on error.\\n\\n## Definitions\\n\\n### Classes / Types\\n| Name | File | Description |\\n|------|------|-------------|\\n| `OpenRouterClient` | `agentic/engine/openrouter.py` | HTTP client for OpenRouter chat-completion API with retry/backoff and normalized response format |\\n| `OpenRouterError` | `agentic/engine/openrouter.py` | Exception for unrecoverable API errors; carries `status_code` attribute |\\n| `LightweightWorkflowSession` | `agentic/engine/runner.py` | Session state container: `context`, `chat_history`, `outputs`, `current_layer` |\\n\\n### Functions\\n| Function | File | Signature | Description |\\n|----------|------|-----------|-------------|\\n| `run_workflow` | `agentic/engine/runner.py` | `(workflow_json, client, tool_registry, input_data) -> dict` | Executes full multi-layer workflow, returns session state dict |\\n| `process_layer` | `agentic/engine/runner.py` | `(layer_def, session, client, tool_registry) -> dict` | Dispatches single layer by `layer_type`: prompt, agentic_loop, smart_template, tool |\\n| `process_agentic_loop` | `agentic/engine/loop.py` | `(layer_def, session, client, tool_registry, knowledge) -> dict` | ReAct-style text-parsed agentic loop with Thought/Action/Answer format |\\n| `process_agentic_loop_native` | `agentic/engine/loop.py` | `(layer_def, session, client, tool_registry, knowledge) -> dict` | Native OpenAI-format function-calling agentic loop |\\n| `summarize_loop` | `agentic/engine/loop.py` | `(chat_history, client, model) -> str` | LLM-generated structured summary of agent conversation |\\n| `execute_tool_call` | `agentic/engine/tool_executor.py` | `(available_tools, tool_name, tool_args) -> str` | Safe tool dispatch with signature-aware argument filtering |\\n| `extract_json` | `agentic/engine/tool_executor.py` | `(response) -> dict \\\\| None` | Extracts JSON from LLM output (thinking blocks → fenced code → brace matching) |\\n| `parse_tool_args` | `agentic/engine/tool_executor.py` | `(raw_args) -> dict` | Multi-strategy argument parsing: JSON → regex key-value → brace matching |\\n| `resolve_knowledge` | `agentic/engine/knowledge.py` | `(rules, skills, knowledge_set, base_dir) -> dict` | Assembles rules_text, rules_index, skills_index for prompt injection |\\n| `discover_skills` | `agentic/engine/knowledge.py` | `(base_dir) -> list[dict]` | Scans for folder-based and JSON-defined skills |\\n| `extract_frontmatter` | `agentic/engine/knowledge.py` | `(file_path) -> dict` | Parses YAML-subset frontmatter from markdown with heuristic fallback |\\n| `build_rules_index` | `agentic/engine/knowledge.py` | `(file_paths) -> str` | Builds `<AVAILABLE_RULES>` XML index from file paths |\\n| `build_skills_index` | `agentic/engine/knowledge.py` | `(metadata) -> str` | Builds `<AVAILABLE_SKILLS>` XML index from skill metadata |\\n| `OpenRouterClient.chat_completion` | `agentic/engine/openrouter.py` | `(model, messages, tools, max_tokens, temperature, stop) -> dict` | Sends chat completion request, returns `{content, tool_calls, usage}` |\\n\\n### Internal helpers (not re-exported)\\n| Function | File | Description |\\n|----------|------|-------------|\\n| `_build_system_message` | `agentic/engine/loop.py` | Assembles system prompt from layer def, knowledge, tool descriptions, and mode-specific format instructions |\\n| `_tool_schemas` | `agentic/engine/loop.py` | Auto-generates OpenAI-format tool schemas from function signatures; respects `tool_schema` attribute |\\n| `_tool_descriptions_text` | `agentic/engine/loop.py` | Builds human-readable tool name + docstring list |\\n| `_resolve_placeholders` | `agentic/engine/runner.py` | Replaces `{PLO}` and `{OutputLayer-N}` legacy tokens |\\n| `_render_jinja` | `agentic/engine/runner.py` | Renders Jinja2 templates with session context (BaseLoader, no filesystem) |\\n| `_process_prompt` | `agentic/engine/runner.py` | Simple prompt layer: template → LLM → response |\\n| `_process_smart_template` | `agentic/engine/runner.py` | Template-only layer, no AI call |\\n| `_process_tool` | `agentic/engine/runner.py` | Direct tool execution layer |\\n| `_filter_args` | `agentic/engine/tool_executor.py` | Introspects function signature, filters args to accepted parameters |\\n| `_extract_braced_json` | `agentic/engine/tool_executor.py` | Brace-counting fallback to find outermost JSON object |\\n| `_parse_frontmatter_block` | `agentic/engine/knowledge.py` | Extracts `---` delimited YAML-subset block |\\n| `_heuristic_meta` | `agentic/engine/knowledge.py` | Derives name/description from first heading + paragraph |\\n\\n## Module Dependencies\\n\\n### This area depends on:\\n| Area/Module | What is used | How |\\n|-------------|-------------|-----|\\n| `jinja2` (external) | `jinja2.Environment`, `jinja2.BaseLoader`, `jinja2.Undefined` | Template rendering in `_render_jinja()` |\\n| `agentic-tools` | Tool callables in `tool_registry` dict | `execute_tool_call()` dispatches to tool `execute()` functions; `loop.py` invokes tools during agentic iterations |\\n\\n### Other areas depend on this:\\n| Area/Module | What they use | How |\\n|-------------|--------------|-----|\\n| `agentic-docs-and-workflows` | `OpenRouterClient`, `LightweightWorkflowSession`, `resolve_knowledge`, `discover_skills`, `run_workflow` | Documentation references; workflow definitions consumed by `run_workflow()