ared system message assembly and automatic conversation summarization.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"agentic/engine/openrouter.py\",\n      \"role\": \"service\",\n      \"exports\": [\n        \"OpenRouterClient\",\n        \"OpenRouterError\",\n        \"_MAX_RETRIES\",\n        \"_BACKOFF_SECONDS\"\n      ],\n      \"imports_from\": [\n        \"json (stdlib)\",\n        \"logging (stdlib)\",\n        \"time (stdlib)\",\n        \"urllib.error (stdlib)\",\n        \"urllib.request (stdlib)\",\n        \"typing.Any (stdlib)\"\n      ],\n      \"key_functions\": [\n        \"OpenRouterClient.__init__(api_key, base_url) \\u2014 Initializes client with API credentials\",\n        \"OpenRouterClient.chat_completion(model, messages, tools, max_tokens, temperature, stop) -> dict \\u2014 Sends chat completion request with retry logic and returns normalized response\",\n        \"OpenRouterClient._post(path, payload) -> dict \\u2014 Internal POST with exponential backoff retry for 429/5xx errors\",\n        \"OpenRouterClient._normalise(raw) -> dict \\u2014 Extracts first choice into flat dict with content, tool_calls, and usage keys\"\n      ],\n      \"patterns\": [\n        \"Retry pattern with exponential backoff\",\n        \"Adapter pattern (normalizes OpenRouter API responses)\",\n        \"Circuit breaker pattern (distinguishes retryable vs non-retryable errors)\"\n      ],\n      \"summary\": \"Lightweight stdlib-only HTTP client for OpenRouter API with automatic retry, exponential backoff, and normalized response format.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"agentic/engine/runner.py\",\n      \"role\": \"controller\",\n      \"exports\": [\n        \"LightweightWorkflowSession\",\n        \"process_layer(layer_def, session, client, tool_registry) -> dict\",\n        \"run_workflow(workflow_json, client, tool_registry, input_data) -> dict\",\n        \"_resolve_placeholders(text, session) -> str\",\n        \"_render_jinja(template_str, context) -> str\",\n        \"_process_prompt(layer_def, session, client) -> dict\",\n        \"_process_smart_template(layer_def, session) -> dict\",\n        \"_process_tool(layer_def, session, tool_registry) -> dict\"\n      ],\n      \"imports_from\": [\n        \"OpenRouterClient from .openrouter\",\n        \"process_agentic_loop, process_agentic_loop_native from .loop\",\n        \"resolve_knowledge from .knowledge\",\n        \"jinja2 (external)\",\n        \"copy (stdlib)\",\n        \"json (stdlib)\",\n        \"logging (stdlib)\",\n        \"re (stdlib)\",\n        \"typing.Any (stdlib)\"\n      ],\n      \"key_functions\": [\n        \"LightweightWorkflowSession \\u2014 Accumulated state class with context, chat_history, outputs, and current_layer tracking\",\n        \"run_workflow(workflow_json, client, tool_registry, input_data) -> dict \\u2014 Executes complete multi-layer workflow, updating session state after each layer\",\n        \"process_layer(layer_def, session, client, tool_registry) -> dict \\u2014 Dispatches layer by layer_type: prompt, agentic_loop, smart_template, or tool\",\n        \"_resolve_placeholders(text, session) -> str \\u2014 Replaces {PLO} and {OutputLayer-N} legacy tokens\",\n        \"_render_jinja(template_str, context) -> str \\u2014 Renders Jinja2 templates with session context using BaseLoader (no filesystem access)\",\n        \"_process_prompt(layer_def, session, client) -> dict \\u2014 Simple prompt layer: template \\u2192 LLM call \\u2192 response\",\n        \"_process_smart_template(layer_def, session) -> dict \\u2014 Template-only layer with no AI call\",\n        \"_process_tool(layer_def, session, tool_registry) -> dict \\u2014 Direct tool execution layer\"\n      ],\n      \"patterns\": [\n        \"Session/state management pattern\",\n        \"Template processing pipeline (legacy placeholders \\u2192 Jinja2)\",\n        \"Layered architecture with dispatcher\",\n        \"Chain of responsibility for layer types\"\n      ],\n      \"summary\": \"Multi-layer workflow orchestrator that manages session state, processes different layer types (prompt, agentic loop, template, tool), and chains outputs between layers.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"agentic/engine/tool_executor.py\",\n      \"role\": \"service\",\n      \"exports\": [\n        \"extract_json(response) -> dict | None\",\n        \"parse_tool_args(raw_args) -> dict\",\n        \"execute_tool_call(available_tools, tool_name, tool_args) -> str\",\n        \"_extract_braced_json(text) -> dict | None\",\n        \"_filter_args(func, args) -> dict\"\n      ],\n      \"imports_from\": [\n        \"inspect (stdlib)\",\n        \"json (stdlib)\",\n        \"logging (stdlib)\",\n        \"re (stdlib)\",\n        \"typing.Any (stdlib)\"\n      ],\n      \"key_functions\": [\n        \"extract_json(response) -> dict | None \\u2014 Extracts JSON from LLM output via  thinking blocks stripping, fenced code blocks, or brace matching\",\n        \"parse_tool_args(raw_args) -> dict \\u2014 Multi-strategy argument parsing: direct JSON, regex key-value pairs, or brace matching\",\n        \"execute_tool_call(available_tools, tool_name, tool_args) -> str \\u2014 Safe tool dispatch with signature-aware argument filtering, returns JSON string\",\n        \"_extract_braced_json(text) -> dict | None \\u2014 Brace-counting fallback to find outermost JSON object\",\n        \"_filter_args(func, args) -> dict \\u2014 Introspects function signature and filters args to match accepted parameters\"\n      ],\n      \"patterns\": [\n        \"Defensive parsing with multiple fallback strategies\",\n        \"Safe execution with signature filtering\",\n        \"Sandbox pattern (args filtered to prevent injection)\"\n      ],\n      \"summary\": \"Safe tool execution utilities that extract structured data from LLM responses and dispatch tool calls with signature-aware argument filtering.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"area_summary\": \"The agentic-engine is a lightweight autonomous AI workflow engine implementing a layered architecture for LLM-powered automation. It provides a multi-layer workflow runner (runner.py) that orchestrates sequential processing steps, dual-mode agentic loops (loop.py) supporting both ReAct text-parsing and native OpenAI function-calling patterns, a stdlib-only OpenRouter HTTP client (openrouter.py) with retry logic, safe tool execution (tool_executor.py) with signature filtering, and a knowledge resolution system (knowledge.py) for discovering and assembling rules/skills into prompts. The engine uses Jinja2 templating, session-based state management, and XML-wrapped knowledge injection to create flexible, composable AI workflows without external dependencies beyond jinja2.\",\n  \"cross_area_refs\": [\n    \"imports jinja2 from external package (runner.py)\",\n    \"imports execute_tool_call from tool_executor (loop.py)\",\n    \"imports OpenRouterClient from openrouter (runner.py, loop.py)\",\n    \"imports process_agentic_loop, process_agentic_loop_native from loop (runner.py)\",\n    \"imports resolve_knowledge from knowledge (runner.py)\"\n  ],\n  \"suggested_splits\": []\n}\n```\n\n## Relationship Edges for This Area\n\n```json\n[\n  {\n    \"from_area\": \"agentic-engine\",\n    \"to_area\": \"agentic-tools\",\n    \"type\": \"calls\",\n    \"details\": \"tool_executor.py dispatches tool calls to tool execute() functions; runner.py passes tool_registry containing agentic-tools modules; loop.py invokes execute_tool_call which calls into tool modules\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"from_area\": \"agentic-docs-and-workflows\",\n    \"to_area\": \"agentic-engine\",\n    \"type\": \"shares_types\",\n    \"details\": \"Documentation references: agentic.engine.run_workflow, agentic.engine.OpenRouterClient, agentic.engine.knowledge.resolve_knowledge, agentic.engine.knowledge.discover_skills, agentic.engine.runner.LightweightWorkflowSession\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"from_area\": \"agentic-engine\",\n    \"to_area\": \"agentic-en