/search_code.py` | `100` | Maximum regex matches before truncation. |\\n| `_SKIP_DIRS` | `agentic/tools/search_code.py` | `{.git, node_modules, __pycache__, .venv, venv, .tox, .mypy_cache}` | Directories to prune during search. |\\n| `_SKIP_DIRS` | `agentic/tools/get_file_tree.py` | `{.git, node_modules, __pycache__, .venv, venv, .tox, .mypy_cache, .pytest_cache, dist, build, .eggs}` | Directories to prune during tree generation (superset of search's list). |\\n| `_SKIP_EXTENSIONS` | `agentic/tools/search_code.py`, `agentic/tools/get_file_tree.py` | `{.pyc, .pyo, .class, .o, .so, .dll, .exe, .bin, .whl}` | Binary file extensions to skip. |\\n\\n## Module Dependencies\\n\\n### This area depends on:\\n| Area/Module | What is used | How |\\n|-------------|-------------|-----|\\n| Python stdlib (`json`, `os`) | JSON serialization, path resolution, file I/O | Imported directly in every tool module |\\n| Python stdlib (`re`, `fnmatch`) | Regex compilation, glob matching | Imported in `search_code.py` only |\\n| Python stdlib (`pathlib.Path`) | Path basename extraction | Imported in `get_file_tree.py` only |\\n\\n### Other areas depend on this:\\n| Area/Module | What they use | How |\\n|-------------|--------------|-----|\\n| `agentic-engine` | All `execute()` functions, `definitions.json` | `tool_executor.py` dispatches tool calls via function paths from `definitions.json`; `runner.py` passes tool registry containing these modules; `loop.py` invokes `execute_tool_call` which calls into tool modules |\\n| `agentic-docs-and-workflows` | Tool references, `definitions.json` schema | Documentation references all five tool modules and the definitions schema |\\n\\n## Shared Types\\n\\n### Tool `execute()` interface (defined here, used by agentic-engine)\\nStandardized signature: `execute(named_params, _base_dir='.', **kwargs) -> str` where the return value is always a JSON string. This is the contract between tool modules and the engine's `tool_executor.py`.\\n\\n### Tool definitions schema (defined here, used by agentic-engine, agentic-docs-and-workflows)\\n`definitions.json` declares each tool's `name`, `description`, `function_path`, and `parameters_schema` (JSON Schema). The `tool_sets` key groups tools into `code_analysis` and `file_ops` sets for workflow composition.\\n\\n## Configuration\\n- **`definitions.json`** — Declarative tool registry. Maps tool names to `function_path` strings (e.g., `agentic.tools.read_file.execute`) and defines parameter schemas. The engine reads this to discover available tools.\\n- **`_base_dir` parameter** — Runtime sandbox root, passed by the engine to constrain all filesystem operations. Not a config file but a runtime injection.\\n\\n## Impact Notes\\n- **`agentic-engine`** is the primary consumer. Changing any `execute()` signature, return format, or `function_path` in `definitions.json` will break tool dispatch in `tool_executor.py`, `runner.py`, and `loop.py`.\\n- **`agentic-docs-and-workflows`** references tool names and schemas. Renaming tools or changing parameter schemas requires updating documentation.\\n- The `_validate_path` function is duplicated across four modules (`read_file`, `write_file`, `list_directory`, `search_code`). A bug fix or behavioral change must be applied to all four copies.\\n- Adding a new tool requires: (1) creating the module with an `execute()` function, (2) adding its entry to `definitions.json`, and (3) optionally adding it to a `tool_sets` group.\\n\\n## Change History\\n> Initial documentation generated by Spark.\\n\",\"kwargs\":\"{}\"}"
