          "arguments": "{\"path\":\".claude/rules/docs/agentic-tools.md\",\"content\":\"# Guanine(CodeEdit) — Agentic Tools Documentation\\n> Auto-generated by Spark. Last updated: 2026-04-06\\n> Source area: agentic-tools\\n\\n## Purpose\\nProvides a sandboxed filesystem and code search toolkit for the agentic engine. Each tool module exposes a standardized `execute()` function that accepts a `_base_dir` parameter for path sandboxing and returns JSON strings for safe inter-process communication. The `definitions.json` serves as a declarative registry enabling dynamic tool discovery and grouping into logical sets (`code_analysis`, `file_ops`).\\n\\n## Data Flows\\n- **Input:** The agentic engine (`tool_executor.py`) dispatches tool calls by importing `execute()` from the function path specified in `definitions.json`, passing named parameters plus `_base_dir` for sandboxing.\\n- **Processing:** Each `execute()` validates the path via `_validate_path()` (resolves symlinks, checks prefix containment), performs the filesystem operation, and catches all exceptions into JSON error responses.\\n- **Output:** Every tool returns a JSON string — either a result payload (`content`, `entries`, `matches`, `tree`, `written`) or an `{\\\"error\\\": \\\"...\\\"}` object.\\n\\n## Invariants Enforced\\n- **Path sandboxing:** All tools resolve paths via `os.path.realpath` and reject any path that escapes `_base_dir`. This prevents directory traversal attacks (e.g., `../../etc/passwd`).\\n- **JSON contract:** Every `execute()` function returns a `str` containing valid JSON — never raises exceptions to the caller.\\n- **Recursive depth limits:** `list_directory` caps recursion at depth 3; `get_file_tree` defaults to depth 4.\\n- **Result truncation:** `search_code` stops after 100 matches (`_MAX_MATCHES`) and sets `\\\"truncated\\\": true`.\\n- **Skip lists:** `search_code` and `get_file_tree` skip common build/cache directories (`.git`, `node_modules`, `__pycache__`, `.venv`, etc.) and